.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype female, IR14-2011: A = palp; B = chelicera; C = gnathosoma. Scale bars = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1013,1758]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[298,398,1013,1037]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">paratype</typeStatus>
) — Similar to male except for the shape of the genital field (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1205,1013,1037]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[168,1383,190,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-71@61.[151,1415,161,1943]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 45A–H. Albia hyporheica sp. nov. (A–B, D–F, H — holotype male, C, G? paratype female from IR22-2011: A = dorsal shield; B-C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = ejaculatory complex; E = gnathosoma; F-G = palp; H = I-L-4-6. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 45C</figureCitation>
). Dorsal shield L/W 423/263; ventral shield L/W 400/281; gnathosomal bay L 71. Genital field not fused with ventral shield; 9 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1353,1367,1050,1074]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">–</emphasis>
10 Ac on each side; acetabular plates L 52 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[558,572,1086,1110]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">–</emphasis>
54; distance between outer margins of acetabular plates 128. Excretory pore and a pair of flanking glandularia lying free in the integument posterior to the genital field. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1343,1121,1145]" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="57.[151,250,916,939]" captionTargetBox="[164,1425,207,887]" captionTargetId="figure-385@57.[151,1436,193,895]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 42A–C. Haloaxonopsis salina sp. nov., paratype female, IR14-2011: A = palp; B = chelicera; C = gnathosoma. Scale bars = 100 µm." pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 42G</figureCitation>
): total L 120, dL: P-1, 16; P-2, 24; P-3, 23; P-4, 41; P-5, 16; L P-2/P-4 ratio, 0.59. Gnathosoma vL 77, chelicera total L 113. Legs: dL of I-L-3–6: 40, 42, 62; dL of IV-L: 72, 38, 51, 72, 72, 59; palp chaetotaxy and swimming setae numbers as in male.
</paragraph>
