<subSubSection box="[199,1017,1265,1290]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1013,1758]" box="[199,1017,1265,1290]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,1266,1290]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for its occurrence in hyporheic waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1013,1758]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[199,315,1302,1326]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1302,1326]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1974" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1974" box="[498,757,1301,1326]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dentalbia">
<emphasis box="[498,610,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Dentalbia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[621,757,1301,1325]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 860" refId="ref32930" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">Cook, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiles, P. R." box="[1032,1154,1301,1325]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="465 - 487" refId="ref34433" refString="Wiles, P. R. (1992) Watermites (Hydrachnidia: Aturidae) of the genus Albia Thon from Asia and Australasia with descriptions of eleven new species. Entomologica Scandinavica, 22, 465 - 487." type="journal article" year="1992">Wiles1992</bibRefCitation>
) by: 1) two glandularia (medially displaced L1 and L2 [
<emphasis box="[533,595,1338,1361]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">sensu</emphasis>
Wiles, 1996]) located on Cx-III; 2) P-2 ventrodistally with 1-3 greatly enlarged setae; and 3) suture line between Cx-III and Cx-IV greatly reduced or absent. This subgenus includes: 
<taxonomicName authority="Viets, 1935" authorityName="Viets" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,469,1409,1434]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paucipora">
<emphasis box="[151,334,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Albia paucipora</emphasis>
Viets, 1935
</taxonomicName>
(
