<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1013,1758]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Due to P-2 with two stout setae ventrodistally and the enlarged leg claws, the new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1326,1371,1482,1505]" name="Iran" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Iran</collectingCountry>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1967" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[358,675,1517,1542]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phreatica">
<emphasis box="[358,533,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Albia phreatica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[541,675,1517,1541]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a hyporheobiontic species known from 
<collectingRegion box="[1137,1340,1517,1541]" country="India" name="Maharashtra" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Maharashtra State</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1378,1435,1517,1541]" name="India" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[158,286,1553,1577]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y." box="[298,617,1553,1578]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="20 - 32" refId="ref33979" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Ranga Reddy, Y. (2009) New records of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from interstitial freshwaters of India, with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 2158, 20 - 32." type="journal article" year="2009">Pešić &amp; Ranga Reddy, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1967" box="[968,1127,1554,1578]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phreaticola">
<emphasis box="[968,1127,1554,1578]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">A. phreaticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the following, in parentheses, data taken from 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[416,541,1589,1613]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 411" refId="ref32903" refString="Cook, D. R. (1967) Water mites from India. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 9, 1 - 411." type="journal article" year="1967">Cook 1967</bibRefCitation>
) in its smaller size (L dorsal shield 460-517, ventral shield 464-517, in the both sexes), the lower number of Ac on each side (13-25 Ac, in the both sexes), and in the glandularia on Cx-III shifted closer to D2 than E2 (closer to E2 than to D2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1437,1013,1758]" box="[199,1080,1697,1722]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1697,1722]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Interstitial waters associated with sand and gravel deposits of stream.
</paragraph>
